article.headline: Harvard 56, Princeton 39
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Collier Winters passed for 403 yards, five touchdowns and rushed for a score to lead Harvard to a 56-39 win against rival Princeton on Saturday. Winters had passing scores of 29, 53, 16 and two 17-yard touchdowns for the Crimson (5-1, 3-0 Ivy League), who have won five straight games. The quarterback, who also had an interception, scored on a 1-yard run to give Harvard a 7-6 lead in the first quarter. Treavor Scales ran for 85 yards and two touchdowns, while Chris Lorditch had six catches for 101 yards and a touchdown for the Crimson. After Winters' early rushing score, Harvard pushed its lead to 35-9 when Alex Sarkisian caught a 16-yard touchdown pass from Winters. The Tigers (1-5, 1-2), who lost their third consecutive game, racked up 556 total yards -- four yards less than their opponent. Chuck Dibilio led Princeton with 135 yards and two touchdowns.
